The paper deals with the foundational and structural aspects of entanglement in quantum systems, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The paper's focus on entanglement and Bell's inequalities suggests that it could be classified under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which includes quantum computing and quantum information. The paper's use of Tsirelson's bound and marginal distribution law suggests that it could also be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper's emphasis on modeling and complex Hilbert space suggests that it could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.QI (Quantum Physics). Finally, the paper's focus on entanglement schemes and non-locality suggests that it could be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
